# Go: EVERY .go is GENERATED (the certified output) — none is ever checked in (the uncommittable-Go seal +
# ocaml-origin gate are the backstops).  `make emit` writes emitdemo/spine_demo.go; `make build` exports
# spine_demo.go to the repo root.
*.go
/fido
*.test
*.out
vendor/

# Environment
.env

# The certified Go output: emitdemo/spine_demo.go is GENERATED on demand by `make emit` (its exact bytes are
# pinned + machine-checked by GoEmit.demo_emit_bytes) and NEVER committed — `make check` regenerates + verifies
# it, so it can never go stale.  The extraction intermediates + the build-generated one-line writer are transient.
/emitdemo/emit_demo.ml
/emitdemo/emit_demo.mli
/emitdemo/gen_write.ml
/emitdemo/*.cmi
/emitdemo/*.cmo
/emitdemo/spine_demo.go

# A stray printer.ml from an old standalone extraction — never tracked
/printer.ml
/printer.mli

# Rocq build artifacts — .v sources are checked in, these are not
*.glob
*.vo
*.vok
*.vos
*.vio
*.aux
.*.aux
.lia.cache
.nia.cache
.coq-native/
_build/
